To comprehensively elucidate potential regulatory mechanisms of systemic metabolic homeostasis, inter-organ metabolic cycles for additional key metabolic organs should be evaluated. Adipose tissue is an obvious choice. We analyzed the trans-omic network of insulin signaling in differentiated 3T3 adipocytes (
 Krycer et al., 2017; 
 Quek et al., 2020; 
 Ohno et al., 2020). We intend to apply our trans-omic approach to investigating inter-organ metabolic cycles between adipose tissue and other organs 
 in vivo in the future.
